original: Broberg, Erik Oskar, tandläkare, Oskarshamn, f. 23/12/04 i Uppsala av godsäg. Oskar B. o. Anna Söderberg. G. 31 m. Märta Hagberg. Barn: Olle f. 40, Kerstin 43. — Stud:ex. i Nyköping 24, tandl:kand. 27, tandläkare 31. Vik. i Skellefteå o. Matfors 30, assist, i Oskarshamn 31-32, praktik där sed. 32, handhade Röda Korsets skoltandv. i Oskarshamn delvis under åren 31-37. Hobby: filateli.
translated: Broberg, Erik Oskar, dentist, from Oskarshamn, born December 23, 1904 in Uppsala to estate owner Oskar B. and Anna Söderberg. Married in 1931 to Märta Hagberg. Children: Olle born in 1940, Kerstin born in 1943. He completed his secondary school education in Nyköping in 1924, graduated from dental school in 1927, and became a licensed dentist in 1931. He worked temporarily in Skellefteå and Matfors in 1930, as an assistant in Oskarshamn in 1931-1932, and then had his own dental practice in Oskarshamn starting in 1932. He partially managed the Swedish Red Cross school dental service in Oskarshamn between 1931-1937. His hobby was philately.

workExperience.name: Swedish Red Cross school dental service
